==Documentation==
This template creates a full genre page layout with hero section, tabs, wiki content, and sidebar.
Uses Semantic MediaWiki for structured data storage and display.

Genres are categories of games based on gameplay mechanics - e.g., First-Person Shooter, RPG, Platformer.

===Parameters===
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Description
|-
|| Name || Display name of the genre
|-
|| Guid || Giant Bomb API identifier
|-
|| Aliases || Alternative names (comma-separated)
|-
|| Image || Genre image filename
|-
|| BackgroundImage || Background image filename
|-
|| Deck || Short description shown in hero
|}

===Usage===
<pre>
{{Genre
| Name = First-Person Shooter
| Guid = 3060-5
| Deck = Games where the player views the world through the protagonist's eyes...
}}

== Overview ==
Your wiki content here...

{{GenreEnd}}
</pre>
